00:32:13,749 --> 00:32:17,309
I mean, the point is that if we accept the notion that there are skills and that the

467
00:32:17,369 --> 00:32:23,150
skills are implicated by discrete gameplay challenges, then it's possible for us as designers

468
00:32:23,190 --> 00:32:27,751
to ensure that the tempo of those challenges is just always beyond the comfort zone of

469
00:32:27,791 --> 00:32:28,391
any one player.

470
00:32:29,331 --> 00:32:30,792
At which point, it's up to the players.

471
00:32:31,358 --> 00:32:33,560
to identify what those compound challenges are,

472
00:32:34,041 --> 00:32:36,162
agree amongst themselves as to who's going to take on what,

473
00:32:36,643 --> 00:32:38,664
and then at that point, it becomes a rather enjoyable

474
00:32:39,085 --> 00:32:40,186
process of overcoming it.

475
00:32:41,607 --> 00:32:44,189
Red Dead Redemption and the Outlast to the End co-op

