00:33:34,172 --> 00:33:38,912
associated with those different styles of play are the same skills. They differ maybe

490
00:33:39,152 --> 00:33:42,853
by one or two skills in a couple different areas. But we didn't really fully explore

491
00:33:42,873 --> 00:33:45,734
or take advantage of this approach. But it's definitely something that we could.

492
00:33:48,914 --> 00:33:52,455
The last dynamic I'm going to talk about is one that I think is probably familiar to people

493
00:33:52,515 --> 00:33:55,475
who have played a lot of the bullet hell style shooter games.

494
00:33:56,071 --> 00:34:02,273
its notion of survival and attrition. And as a dynamic, it really is a kind of oscillation

495
00:34:02,974 --> 00:34:08,376
in terms of player motive. So it's almost at the level of metagame. It's the notion

496
00:34:08,436 --> 00:34:15,118
that play can continue for as long as there is at least one player alive, which is essentially

497
00:34:15,178 --> 00:34:18,280
saying you can be a hero, but you can also be dead.

498
00:34:22,034 --> 00:34:25,977
many players are possible, or many survivors are possible. In fact, all the players could

