00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:55,721
Now initially, players would mark targets because it was a great way to communicate

530
00:36:55,761 --> 00:36:58,801
with each other. It was a great way to say, oh, hey, there's a guy over there. He just

531
00:36:58,821 --> 00:37:03,902
walked around that, oh, there, okay, there he is. And then that created an opportunity

532
00:37:04,642 --> 00:37:08,083
as players were earning execute tokens for each other by taking enemies out hand to hand

