00:40:50,880 --> 00:40:53,341
were buddies and then, well, I'm not going to spoil the ending.

592
00:40:56,263 --> 00:41:03,867
So just to kind of go over some generalized best practices in order to wrap up, I think

593
00:41:04,267 --> 00:41:06,288
the first thing is, if you don't have to...

594
00:41:07,436 --> 00:41:10,699
Try not to pour production values into highly prescriptive systems.

595
00:41:11,500 --> 00:41:13,241
Alright? You're not fooling your players.

596
00:41:14,502 --> 00:41:17,625
If you stick an invisible collision or a glowing wall or whatever it is,

597
00:41:18,165 --> 00:41:20,568
your players will understand what it is.

598
00:41:20,668 --> 00:41:24,171
They'll realize what you've done and they'll understand that you had a reason for doing it.

599
00:41:24,311 --> 00:41:26,993
They might not like it, but they'll move on.

600
00:41:28,615 --> 00:41:33,679
If you attempt to make it look as though everything is normal and okay,

601
00:41:34,389 --> 00:41:38,511
then they are going to bump into that collision in a more painful way because they will be

602
00:41:38,571 --> 00:41:43,374
trying to use their collective agency. They'll be talking to each other. Wait, no, maybe

603
00:41:43,394 --> 00:41:45,915
we need to go around to the left. Okay, you try going to the right. Okay, see if you hit

604
00:41:45,935 --> 00:41:51,259
that. Okay. No, actually, no, you're just not allowed to do that. So better to go the

605
00:41:51,299 --> 00:41:56,201
gamey route and embrace it and have them deal with it than to try to convince them something

606
00:41:56,241 --> 00:42:03,726
else is happening. Whether or not you agree with any of the dynamics that I've described,

607
00:42:04,386 --> 00:42:08,389
just please, my appeal to you is give the players tools for mutual support. You can

